posts.title: Bolt Logo
posts.content:
There was a hand in the light, and it held a flower. The woman carrying the rose was petite. Dark haired, and fair of skin, she wore a deep-red dress.The rose, however, was as white as fresh snow. She held it in front of her, smiling.

The other woman standing in front of her took the rose, examined it. Though the way she handled it made her accidentally prick her finger. “No!” she cried. Her hands began to tremble, then it spread to her arms and to her shoulders. She dropped the rose as the shaking spread throughout her body. She looked at the petite woman who smiled, and revealed bloody teeth.

The shaking was too much to bear. Her legs gave in and she fell on the ground. “No…” she whispered again as the bloody teeth came closer. “…n…” she barely let out before the world faded to black.
posts.excerpt: There was a hand in the light, and it held a flower. The woman carrying the rose was petite. Dark haired, and fair of skin, she wore a deep-red dress.

posts.title: We need to talk about streetwear
posts.content:
The great mind behind streetwear line opens his heart in this tear-jerking interview. What fears lie behind those hazel eyes? What does he think about before going to sleep? And what makes him wake up in the morning? Hint: it’s not clothes..

 

Jeremiah weighs the cup of coffee in his hands. Black, no milk, no sugar. Pure and bitter as life. I can  feel the spring breeze as we finish up our breakfast. The usual platter of fruit, vegetables and the best eggs Benedict I’ve had.

After thanking him for the meal, I ask about what keeps him up at night. He nods, weighs the cup a little more before speaking.

There so much history behind his clothing brand. It was born out of the skate, hip hop, art, social consciousness, and youth fashion culture in New York City around 1995. The name references 10 fingers, the average number of which each person has on his or her hands.

His collections had simple tees and cut and sew tops. But it grew as rapidly as the culture around it did. There’s an inherent dependancy his brand has on that culture. It leans heavily and gathers great inspiration from it.

But as with all culture movements, none last forever. Will the demise of the scene mean the demise of Jeremiah’s store as well?

I anxiously repeat the question. Then I devour another plate of orange marmalade and blue cheese.

posts.title: Number 137
posts.content:
The fine structure constant, a dimensionless physical constant, is approximately 1/137, and the astronomer Arthur Eddington conjectured in 1929 that its reciprocal was in fact precisely the integer 137, which he claimed could be “obtained by pure deduction

On the other hand, we denounce with righteous indignation and dislike men who are so beguiled and demoralized by the charms of pleasure of the moment, so blinded by desire, that they cannot foresee the pain and trouble that are bound to ensue; and equal blame belongs to those who fail in their duty through weakness of will, which is the same as saying through shrinking from toil and pain. These cases are perfectly simple and easy to distinguish.

In a free hour, when our power of choice is untrammelled and when nothing prevents our being able to do what we like best, every pleasure is to be welcomed and every pain avoided. But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures, or else he endures pains to avoid worse pains.

posts.title: Danube’s greatest on sensuality
posts.content:
Our persona non grata is incredible. His work was featured in countless magazine, brochures, and of course Tumblr. He was born in 1989, in Dunaujvaros, Hungary. When Adele sings her song Hello, and references a town in which nothing ever happens, Dunaujvaros is the town she sings about..

The malcontent he-who-must-not-be-mentioned felt the same for Dunaujvaros, and finally moved to Budapest in the early 2010’s. This, in turn, had a profound impact on his social life, which led to a synthesis of visual influences. His pictures constantly depict the relationship between his subjects and the very essence of the space around them.

He flirts with the grotesque nature of each location. This titillating effect tickles the mind of the viewer, and in turn forms a relationship with the work and the viewer.

posts.title: A Monochromatic Spring
posts.content:
New collection from the creative studio and brand label Over got to see it’s Spring ’15 release, wearing the name “A Monochromatic Spring” which is by our opinion a very accurate depiction.

The collection features various simple essentials for both ladies and men, full of strong graphics and patterns inspired and guided by a monochromatic palette.

You can view their new collection, as well as their old releases on www.overclothing.com

The simple start of Over was fueled from personal demand and the basic desire of having something different and unique.

Design remains the driving force behind our work we do at Over, which is run by a small group of local creatives from different fields, united with passion for the things they make.

Without it’s current name, concept and the thought of a wide audience consumption, the whole t-shirt story began it’s life in 2005, through a small scope of people who would preorder the tee’s as they circled around in an email attach. As the people wore the tee’s, a desire from the larger crowd came along, which became a deciding factor for the project going public in 2012.

posts.title: We do not deserve this T-shirt journal
posts.content:
T-world is amazing. Comprised of T-shirt artists from all over the globe, it features works by individuals, brands, and designers all over this blue marble we call home. And it’s so good it should be banned.

Hardcover T-shirt design porn. That’s one way of calling this deluxe journal that feature the current, past, and future T-shirt culture, its influences and executions.

The pages within are teeming with exquisitely designed layouts. It’s bursting with thoughtful interviews with the leading authorities of contemporary T-shirt design. This is literally the only T-shirt bible of its kind available for everyone. From budding designers to seasoned pros, this journal will leave you gagging and begging for more!

posts.title: Pattern use in the apparel industry today
posts.content:
Patterns initially are made in only one size. In order to produce clothing that fits various body types and sizes, the pattern pieces must be increased or decreased geometrically to create a complete range of sizes. The process of resizing the initial pattern is called “grading.” For example, the sample size 10 patterns must be made larger to accommodate sizes 12, 14 and 16 and smaller for sizes 8 and 6.

Pattern grading is the scaling of a pattern to a different size by implementing important points of the pattern using an algorithm in the clothing and footwear industry.

What is the purpose of grading clothing patterns? The purpose of grading is to proportionally increase or decrease the size of a pattern, while maintaining shape, fit, balance, and scale of the garment. Historically, the science of grading went hand-in-hand with the advent of commercial patterns and the mass-production of pattern-built clothing some 150 years ago. To properly fit a pattern to a range of sizes, each pattern piece needed to be graded, or systematically increased or decreased. Today, pattern companies and apparel manufacturers take a middle-sized pattern (for example size Medium) and grade it up for larger sizes and grade it down for smaller sizes.

Grading apparel has primarily three different methods that are often used in the fashion industry. Whether you want to take your favorite pattern up (or down) a size or two or if you want to create new collection of clothing, pattern grading is an important process. Once you understand the nuances, you’ll be able to take your sewing to the next level. With proper pattern grading techniques, a home sewer, custom dressmaker, novice, or professional fashion designer design incredibly well designed clothing.
